'''Alison Vincent''' is the [[Chief Technology Officer]] for [[Cisco]] in the UK and Ireland.<ref name=FDM/>

Vincent worked for [[Cisco Videoscape|NDS]] before it was acquired by Cisco in 2012 and has worked for Cisco since then. Previously, she worked at [[IBM]] and at [[Micro Focus]].<ref name="Cisco blog">{{cite web|title=Alison Vincent|url=https://gblogs.cisco.com/uki/author/alivince/?doing_wp_cron=1507667199.5816988945007324218750|website=Cisco UK & Ireland Blog|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref> She specializes in introducing [[Agile software development|agile]] methodologies to organizations.<ref name="Tech Partnership">{{cite web|last1=Vincent|first1=Alison|title=I saw how computers could change the world and I wanted to be part of that|url=https://www.thetechpartnership.com/inspire/my-tech-story/professional-stories/alisons-story/|website=Tech Partnership|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="Cisco blog" />

She holds a PhD in Mathematics and Cryptography and a BSc in Mathematics and Computer Science from [[Royal Holloway, University of London]].<ref name="Cisco blog" /><ref name="Tech Partnership" /><ref name="Royal Holloway">{{cite web|title=Career profiles|url=https://www.royalholloway.ac.uk/computerscience/women/profiles.aspx|website=Royal Holloway University of London|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref>

