vember 2010 | journal = [[Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society]] | year = 2014 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>
Campbell-Kelly has served on the [[editorial board]] of the ''[[IEEE Annals of the History of Computing]]'' journal. He is a committee member of the [[Computer Conservation Society]], a Specialist Group of the [[British Computer Society]].<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/profile/martin-campbell-kelly Martin Campbell-Kelly] his obituaries of prominent computer science figures in ''[[The Guardian]]''</ref><ref>[http://www.gresham.ac.uk/lectures-and-events/past?keys=&field_speakers_nid=1188&field_lecture_date%5Bvalue%5D%5Byear%5D=&term_node_tid_depth=All Lectures by Martin Campbell-Kelly] available from [[Gresham College]]</ref><ref>{{AcademicSearch|1987427}}</ref>
==Education== Campell-Kelly was educated at [[University of Sunderland|Sunderland Polytechnic]] where he was awarded a PhD in 1980 on the ''Foundations of computer programming in Britain 1945–1955''.<ref>{{cite thesis| degree=PhD | publisher=[[Sunderland Polytechnic]] | title=Foundations of computer programming in Britain 1945–1955 |first= Martin.| last=Campbell-Kelly | date=1980 | url=http://ethos.bl.uk/OrderDetails.do?uin=uk.bl.ethos.253210 | oclc=}}</ref>
==Research== Campbell-Kelly has authored, edited numerous books and journal articles on the history of computing.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?as_auth=Martin+Campbell+Kelly&source=an&ei=W9TVSqi6GKC6jAec8tn9CQ&sa=X&oi=book_group&ct=title&cad=author-navigational&resnum=5&ved=0CCEQsAMwBA Books by Martin Campbell-Kelly], [[Google Books]].</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Martin Campbell-Kelly|title=ICL: A Business and Technical History|publisher=Clarendon: [[Oxford University Press]]|date=1989|pages=409|isbn=0-19-853918-5|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=05K1AAAAIAAJ}}</ref><ref>Martin Campbell-Kelly and William Aspray (1996). ''[[Computer: A History of the Information Machine]]'', [[Basic Books]]/[[HarperCollins]]. {{ISBN|0-465-02989-2}}.</ref><ref>{{cite book|editors=Martin Campbell-Kelly, Mary Croarken, [[Raymond Flood (mathematician)|Raymond Flood]], [[Eleanor Robson]]|title=The History of Mathematical Tables|publisher=Oxford University Press|date=2003|pages=137|isbn=978-0-19-850841-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O170gWPZ7M8C&pg=PA137}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url = http://www.rutherfordjournal.org/article010105.html |title = The User-friendly Typewriter |author = Martin Campbell-Kelly |date=December 2005 | journal = [[The Rutherford Journal]] | volume = 1}}</ref><ref>[http://www.scientificamerican.com/author.cfm?id=2118 Martin Campbell-Kelly] (September 2009). [http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=origin-of-computing The Origin of Computing], ''[[Scientific American]]''.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Campbell-Kelly | first1 = M. | authorlink = Martin Campbell-Kelly| doi = 10.1098/rsbm.2006.0030 | title = [[David Wheeler (computer scientist)|David John Wheeler]]. 9 February 1927 -- 13 December 2004: Elected FRS 1981 | journal = [[Biographical Memoirs of Fellows of the Royal Society]] | volume = 52 | pages = 437 | year = 2006 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>
